commit 019392c193bfeb8af59d36ca020a2800b769ff80
Author: luxgrain <luxgrain@users.noreply.github.com>
Date:   Tue Apr 21 22:05:58 2026 +0900

    iop: add fft_notch + GALOSH algorithm in rawdenoise
    
    New IOP: fft_notch (Bayer CFA FFT band-stop, per darktable_ai).  Sits
    between hotpixels and rawdenoise to remove periodic sensor banding
    (fixed-pattern readout) before stochastic denoise sees the noise
    floor.  Links libfftw3f.  No-op on X-Trans (6x6 super-pixel makes
    the per-slot split non-trivial).
    
    iop_order: rawdenoise moved to priority 4.0f so the raw denoise chain
      3.0  hotpixels
      3.5  fft_notch  (NEW)
      4.0  rawdenoise
      5.0  cacorrect
      6.0  temperature
      7.0  highlights
    runs with Poisson-Gauss noise statistics intact (pre-WB, pre-highlight
    clipping).  Applied to legacy_order, v30_order, v50_order; JPG
    pipelines are unaffected.
    
    rawdenoise: add "algorithm" dropdown (introspection v2 -> v3).
      - DT_IOP_RAWDENOISE_ALGO_WAVELET (default) -> existing wavelet path.
      - DT_IOP_RAWDENOISE_ALGO_GALOSH            -> GAT + 2x2 WHT L/C +
        LOSH(luma) + LOESS(chroma), fully blind Foi+Alenius noise
        estimation.  X-Trans falls back to wavelet.
    
    GALOSH bundled as two headers under src/iop/:
      - galosh_core.h   (1300+ lines) — noise estimation, GAT forward/
        inverse LUT, 8x8 WHT + 2-pass LOSH, LOESS guided chroma.  Same
        file as GALOSH/standalone; new GALOSH_DT_ENV guard suppresses the
        standalone compatibility stubs (gboolean/dt_iop_roi_t/dt_alloc_*/
        CLAMP/MIN/MAX) so darktable's native definitions take precedence.
      - galosh_bayer.h  (1050 lines) — raw Bayer driver
        (CFA-protected DC, 2x2 WHT decompose/reconstruct, compute_L_full-
        res, gat_galosh_denoise_rawlc).  Header-only; static functions
        compile once into rawdenoise's translation unit.
    
    legacy_params v2 -> v3 defaults `algorithm = WAVELET` so every
    existing edit keeps rendering identically until the user explicitly
    picks GALOSH from the new dropdown.
    
    Co-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.7 (1M context) <noreply@anthropic.com>

